task_description: Facing the building to your North (approx. 4°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: To estimate the building's height, I need to see its full vertical extent; rotating upward will reveal the roofline while maintaining alignment with the building's center.
To capture the building's full vertical extent, I need to see both the roof (already visible at 30° up) and the ground level; rotating downward will reveal the base for height calculation.
The building's base is visible at 60° down and roof at 30° up, creating a 90° vertical span; using the 4.8m front-left node distance, trigonometry estimates height as ~11.1m.
